Class User

    Equivalent

    public class User
extends MirandaObject
    A user of the Miranda system.

    Attributes

    Name Type Description
    name String The name of the user.

    This must be unique across all Users in the sytem.

    category enum The category of the user.

    Allowable values are Publisher, Subscriber and Admin. Unknown should not be used but is there for completeness.

    Publishers can create topics and Events.

    Subscribers can create Subscriptions.

    Admins can do anything.

    Users with a category of Unknown cannot do anything.

    description String A user friendly description of the User.
    publicKey PublicKey The public key associated with the user.

    The public key is used during logins to encrypt the session ID sent back to the user. The user uses their private key in all their requests.

        public void copyFrom(Mergeable mergeable)
        Description copied from class: Mergeable
        Copy all attributes from another instance.

        After invoking this method, this instance should be Object.equals(Object) equivalent to the object passed to it.

        The argument should be of the same class as this instance.

        Any subclasses should copy their attributes.

        Specified by:
        copyFrom in class Mergeable
        Parameters:
        mergeable - Another non-null instance that this object should copy from. The object should be of the same type as this instance --- casting to the type of the receiver should work.

      • isEquivalentTo

        public boolean isEquivalentTo(java.lang.Object o)
        Description copied from interface: Equivalent
        Return true if the receiver refers to the same thing as the argument.

        Two instances are equivalent if

        • The have the same class
        • Their "primary keys" are the same

        For example, if two users have the same user name, they are equivalent, but if the user has changed their email address then equals will return false.

        Parameters:
        o - The other instance to compare against.
        Returns:
        True if the other instance is equivalent to the receiver, false otherwise.
